<Time>1598469751170<//Time>< review>
The wine was good and the outdoor seating is shady, perfect for hot days. The customer service is horrible. They bring your wine tastings out all at one time and make no mention of it beforehand. We each got a tasting so they brought out 15 glasses of wine tastes. By the time we got to the last one, it was hot and the flies were after it. The female waitress didn't smile once or come to check on us after bringing out the tastings. She didn't explain any of the wine to us or give us any info at all. We intended to purchase a few bottles but no one ever came back. Sad to have such terrible wait staff in the middle of a pandemic when I'm sure the owners can use all the sales they can get.<//review>

< Text>
This is a place for the Sichuan style BBQ/grilled fish hotpot (a casserole style dish). The only difference is that the whole fish is not grilled, but deep fried. You pick the sauce, then the sides that gets added to the "hotpot". It comes out on a rectangular pan. Tip: Go for the proper mala "peppercorn" sauce, maximum heat and order a couple of beers to go with it. If you want more authentic reference, go to ChongQing or ChengDu.</Text>

<Review>So very sad. I'm 53 and I remember my father bringing me here as a boy when he got his tires. I appreciated Mike for his no-nonsense gruff attitude, telling it like it is. Its one thing to yell at someone who has made a mistake or not held true to their word, but lately he yells and hangs up on customers even while admitting its his fault.

I can understand its a hard business and at 70 you would rather be fishing. I can understand it sucks to have family member (employee) with substance issues, or whatever leads them to make a mistake.

I don't understand why I am to be yelled at and hung up on, twice, for expecting recovery from an employee mistake in a timely and graceful manner. When an owner admits a mistake has been made and promises to call me, I expect a call. <Gmap_id>0x80c2873807adccef:0x153c88594b9507ca< /Gmap_id><Review>Mike made an unfortunate situation much better. I highly recommend this shop! Read more for the story.
My car's CV axle started to go out on the way from Utah to California. I made it to California by sheer faith. I took the car to Mike's the day after we got in. After meeting Mike, he promised me a free diagnostic. He handed me off to Otto, who found the issue quickly and confirmed that it was the axle. Here's the best part: He quoted me FAR less than I expected! I brought the part to them, and they installed it for only 140 dollars! I drive a Volvo XC90, and believe me, the job is NOT easy. The cherry on top: they aligned the car for me at NO extra cost. So, all said and done, I was only out 140 dollars. Mike is a gruff guy, but my experience with him is that he does honest work. I cannot complement him enough. As I said, I also worked with Otto, who took me out to the pit to look at my car on the lift to show me exactly what the problem was (a ripped CV joint boot that lost all it's grease and caused the joint to begin to fail). Otto was incredible. He worked quickly and was incredibly nice. I also got to meet Ben, who was also very nice and good to work with. All in all, I can understand people thinking Mike is a grump, but I don't go to a mechanic to have a friendly conversation. I go to get my car fixed for the cheapest price I can get, while trusting that the work done will be quality. That is exactly what I got when I got to meet Mike this past weekend.< /Review><userid>112461708833345079826< /userid>< pictures>

I‚Äôve taken my two cars to him on numerous occasions over the past two or three years. < review>
Had a packaged shipped to one of their UPS store locations in Las Vegas to be forwarded. The UPS store in question is the one on 4132 S Rainbow Blvd, Las Vegas, NV 89103.

The package arrived with a hold on the side and the item inside was damaged and parts are missing. Not to fault the UPS store for the damaged shipment but UPS. A claim was filed...

After I filed the claim I found out the the UPS Store completely failed to do their job. They failed to insure my package and said I decline it! What! Why would I decline to insure an $1800 item when the insurance is 1/100th of the cost of the item? Shipping alone was 10 times of the insurance!

The UPS store agent did not handle my transaction professionally and failed to fill out my shipping form correctly and completely. In response to the claim the owner of the UPS store said I declined to purchase insurance. That is a lie!

There was no communications from the UPS Store during the claim process at all, none! I had to follow up every week for 3 month until I was issued a low blow claim check of $2xx to cover my $1800 item. Not only that they didn't get my name right and didn't even have my address! Again, that says a lot about their attention to detail.

Now 5 month later I still don't have a proper low blow claim check that I can deposit.

You should shut down this UPS Store for the horrific customer service and not completing their basic job duties!< /review>

UPS Store#2302-Harleysville PA-Tim Twofiles(store manager)

I have always valued the UPS Store customer service and professionalism to handle my shipping needs. I never had a problem with bringing items for them to pack and ship. <gmap_id>0x80dc0769ebaac827:0x1c02116651a370cb<//gmap_id>< review>
CAUTION:  Multiple challenges and unexpected time/cost increases when using UPS for helping with your move!  We used UPS to ship 13 boxes from Denver to NYC.  To summarize, I spent at least 3-4 extra hours with their customer support and website, I was billed inappropriately twice, their systems do not support a good customer experience.

Here's the details of the experience:
- We used UPS website to set up shipment including window (data/time) for pickup and received a quote for cost.
- 90 minutes after the pickup window had passed, we called UPS customer service to find out what was up.  We were told that there was no pickup scheduled and were asked to provide a "Pickup Request Number (PCN)".  When we originally scheduled, we did not receive an email with a PCN, nor was a PCN available when we logged into our online account where we placed the shipping order, so we had no way of providing a PCN.  UPS customer service told us they would schedule another pickup, but they would have to charge us another separate pickup charge and then after the charges came through on our credit card it would be up to us to call their billing department to dispute the charges a week later!!!   Additionally, since it was a Saturday, they wouldn't be able to pick up until Monday between 9am-1pm, delaying our planned shipment.
- After all of that, about two hours later (3+ hours after our pickup window), a UPS truck showed up to pick up our 13 boxes.  The driver told us we had always been on his schedule that day, but was just running way behind!!   Clearly UPS customer service systems and customer website do not have the same information as used by their internal operations.
- Once our shipment was at the UPS warehouse and scanned into their system, we were able to go to the website and select a desired delivery date in NYC.  There was a fee for this, but we were ok with that.  The problem was their website doesn't allow you to pay the fee for your shipment.  You have to submit your credit card information 13 times (one for each box) and pay 13 different delivery fees!
- The shipment was delivered as scheduled and boxes were in good shape.
- After all this, I received an email notice that I was being charged an additional $69 because some of the boxes were 1" larger on one dimension or weighed more than I originally estimated on my shipment.  My problem with this:  1) The boxes were moving boxes from Lowes with exact dimensions.  2)  They only upcharged me for boxes that were a little heavier, but did not reduce the cost for boxes that ended up being 20+ lbs lighter than I provided.  I know my overall shipment weight was at least 50-100 lbs lighter than the total I provided originally!
- I haven't yet attempted to get my charges adjusted.  They wear you down with all the time and effort required to get what's right, but I'll take a run at that sometime soon.< /review>

Without any consideration or loyalty for the employees, corporate expects the employees to kowtow, kiss behind, bend over backward and placate any and all entitled, rude, down trodden, putrid smelling, brainless, obnoxious, abusive, violent individual. You can see why corporate would side with such individuals, after all birds of a feather...

Corporate's disloyalty toward the employees can be far worse for the product in the long run because when the employee tells all of his or her family and friends to boycott, it will create a much greater loss for The UPS Store than the loss of that one drop off customer who was never going to return again anyway, or that one page copy customer who could not wait his turn for the associate to become available to assist.  The loss of that one time $3 in revenue should not outweigh the loss of a good employee who does not deserve abuse from within and without. < review>
I was never much of a Dominos fan until they redid their crust some years back. Now I usually go with them on pizza nights since it's tasty and the pricing is good for a baller on a budget like myself. Bear in mind I have lower standards for most food types...a couple years of the top ramen lifestyle a while back really lowered the bar for me.

The Carp store is simple and clean, and so far the employees have been mostly friendly and cool. Haven't had any mistakes with an order yet (I usually order online and do pickup). Have had issues in the past with ordering via the phone but it's been so long I don't wan't to definitively state any lack of service.< /review>

<text>Chronology of events (latest to earliest)
Encounter 3: Jan 2021: 2nd Furnace purchased (1st purchase as noted below, 2 AC Compressors + 1 Furnace)

4.5 **** for their service techs (mostly excellent, knowledgeable, helpful, and goes the extra mile, with very few exceptions) Khaled continues to excel whenever he comes to service the equipment
3.5 *** for their installation techs. This time, they failed to ground the furnace and disconnect box - basic items that "should" to be done right the first time?! As a result, the "impossible to get hold of SJ City Inspection" failed, and more hassles to get the equipment certified.
3.0*** for the Customer Service - very friendly people, but not knowledgeable and has absolutely no power over their tyrannical Tech Dept. They will give many platitudes to placate the customer, but advise is to immediately request to talk to Tech Dept, otherwise one would have to repeat multiple times the same inputs since the Tech Dept almost never calls back after CS promises they will.
1.5** for Tech Dept. Does not call back until multiple escalation is made. Comes across as arrogant, not particularly helpful. They will fix the problem they created but only after one manages to get to them. (Monica seems to be the only responsive one in that department, Tye has not called back or responded at all both the times I had issues)
0.5* Sales. They will promise you the world, but disappears after the sale. In both my purchases, my Salesman promised a smooth process (ie installation and paperwork specifics - I was clear with my concerns then, and for this latest purchase, especially with the city certification, knowing the grief SJ City will cause). In the first case, they put it down to a "miscommunication" but they finally helped (after escalation) with the City Inspection.  Despite committing to "take care of inspection process and make it transparent to me", during the sales process, now I have a problem with City inspection, and they are nowhere to be found. I have called them but no call back, no sign of anything.

Now, I might expect Alicia or their CS manager to respond to this - seems like the response happens only the customer is extremely annoyed.

So should you go with them? IMHO for general maintenance, if you are not too particular about pricing, a convenient approach.
For new systems, imho "caveat emptor". Some days, you can be made to feel you are the center of their service. Other days just feel like it is too much work to be worth it. (like now)

But as a reminder to myself - I won't be silly to look here for my third upgrade! I really have to stop being so trusting!

Encounter 2: Oct 2019 >>Installation of 2 New ACs/1 Furnace + remedial work on missed installation items-failed City Inspection + subsequent maintenance work
** Update after multiple interactions... Not quite 5 Stars.. service and competency level varied across techs. Some problems encountered: installation of ac compressors not to city code. Minor rework needed. Missed a scheduled appointment totally. New ac compressor not cooling after 6 months. (imagine an approx $10k equipment not working after 6months!) LeamkimgLeaking coolant that couldn't be traced. No dye available to inject to trace leakage, have to return to redo. Problems to be expected but it just means tying up my time waiting for appointments, which I have to follow up on (did not call back to reschedule as promised) To be fair reasonably responsive, although their CS not very capable beyond the superficial greetings and perhaps scheduling work (even then).

Encounter 1: Fall 2019 :Service maintenance on old AC/Heaters
Khaled was the tech that helped me out today. Very timely, detailed in checking out all the issues and helpful with suggestions. Made very good observations and was very polite and kind.

This company seems to have done a good job training their staff and they seem to know what they are doing. Good job!</text>< Response>

< Text>
Chronology of events (latest to earliest)
Encounter 3: Jan 2021: 2nd Furnace purchased (1st purchase as noted below, 2 AC Compressors + 1 Furnace)

4.5 **** for their service techs (mostly excellent, knowledgeable, helpful, and goes the extra mile, with very few exceptions) Khaled continues to excel whenever he comes to service the equipment
3.5 *** for their installation techs. This time, they failed to ground the furnace and disconnect box - basic items that "should" to be done right the first time?! As a result, the "impossible to get hold of SJ City Inspection" failed, and more hassles to get the equipment certified.
3.0*** for the Customer Service - very friendly people, but not knowledgeable and has absolutely no power over their tyrannical Tech Dept. They will give many platitudes to placate the customer, but advise is to immediately request to talk to Tech Dept, otherwise one would have to repeat multiple times the same inputs since the Tech Dept almost never calls back after CS promises they will.
1.5** for Tech Dept. Does not call back until multiple escalation is made. Comes across as arrogant, not particularly helpful. They will fix the problem they created but only after one manages to get to them. (Monica seems to be the only responsive one in that department, Tye has not called back or responded at all both the times I had issues)
0.5* Sales. They will promise you the world, but disappears after the sale. In both my purchases, my Salesman promised a smooth process (ie installation and paperwork specifics - I was clear with my concerns then, and for this latest purchase, especially with the city certification, knowing the grief SJ City will cause). In the first case, they put it down to a "miscommunication" but they finally helped (after escalation) with the City Inspection.  Despite committing to "take care of inspection process and make it transparent to me", during the sales process, now I have a problem with City inspection, and they are nowhere to be found. I have called them but no call back, no sign of anything.

Now, I might expect Alicia or their CS manager to respond to this - seems like the response happens only the customer is extremely annoyed.

So should you go with them? IMHO for general maintenance, if you are not too particular about pricing, a convenient approach.
For new systems, imho "caveat emptor". Some days, you can be made to feel you are the center of their service. Other days just feel like it is too much work to be worth it. (like now)

But as a reminder to myself - I won't be silly to look here for my third upgrade! I really have to stop being so trusting!

Encounter 2: Oct 2019 >>Installation of 2 New ACs/1 Furnace + remedial work on missed installation items-failed City Inspection + subsequent maintenance work
** Update after multiple interactions... Not quite 5 Stars.. service and competency level varied across techs. Some problems encountered: installation of ac compressors not to city code. Minor rework needed. Missed a scheduled appointment totally. New ac compressor not cooling after 6 months. (imagine an approx $10k equipment not working after 6months!) LeamkimgLeaking coolant that couldn't be traced. No dye available to inject to trace leakage, have to return to redo. Problems to be expected but it just means tying up my time waiting for appointments, which I have to follow up on (did not call back to reschedule as promised) To be fair reasonably responsive, although their CS not very capable beyond the superficial greetings and perhaps scheduling work (even then).

Encounter 1: Fall 2019 :Service maintenance on old AC/Heaters
Khaled was the tech that helped me out today. Very timely, detailed in checking out all the issues and helpful with suggestions. Made very good observations and was very polite and kind.

This company seems to have done a good job training their staff and they seem to know what they are doing. Good job!<//Text>

< Review>
During Travis's visit my son left the house & kicked the filter that was sitting on the sidewalk outside the front door. It hit the main sprinkler system & broke two of the PVC pipe heads right off.  Water was spraying everywhere. Travis came down off the roof, found the main water valve & turned off the water.  After he completed his survey of my HVAC system he helped me re-tape the air filter that had come apart with proper tape. He then went to his truck to pull out a box of PVC pipes, cutters and proper glue.  He was able to immediately replace the two heads that were torn off and get our water running again.  I really appreciated his graciousness while I was dealing with a very personal adverse situation that had really upset me. I greatly appreciated his willingness to go the extra mile.  We would have gone without water until I could have gotten an emergency plumber and, paid extra money to have the pipes fixed.  He did it in minutes!  My son was truly sorry to have caused such a problem.

Travis, thank you again for your service, you're the best!

Respectfully,

Mary Debord</Review>

< review>
When our Amana furnace heat exchanger was diagnosed with hairline cracks by our regular service company, we asked Service Champions to give us a second opinion.

On 10/10, Tyler Shook inspected our heater and did not find a failure but showed me that it was worn and stressed after 17 years of use. I asked to speak with a salesman, so he called his office and Chris Lucas arrived a few minutes later. Both Chris and Tyler spent 2 hours helping me choose a new heat pump/furnace system that fit well with our existing solar panel installation. I was very pleased with the knowledge and care that Tyler and Chris showed in helping me find the best/efficient  system to fit our budget.

Washington Dang arrived on 10/13 with his assistant to install our new HVAC system. They both worked steadily for 11 hours to complete the work and explain the system to us. We are very pleased with our new system and the way it was installed by Washington,  We look forward to it passing inspection and testing by the City of Pleasant Hill. Tyler, Chris, and Washington all did very well for me and Service Champions.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2/8/19 Candace Baca did a great job yesterday with her inspection, evaluation and presentation of repair or replacement of our HVAC duct system. Based on her presentation, we have decided to go with the full replacement alternative.  Thanks Candace!</review>

<Rate>4</Rate><Text>Had my furnace replaced by Service Champions on 9/27/2016.
First I want to get on the record  that the two installers were curteous, professional, respectful and knowledgable.
The SC moto is if you are not happy its free! Im not looking for anything free but do want to share my total expertience. I told both men that I was extremely picky and expected the quality of the removal and installation to be perfect; quality of workmanship, cleanliness, protection of surrounding infrastructure, door jams interion of heater closet and enrty / exit doorway etc.
There were three issues with the installation that I was not happy with.
1. The door jams and interior cabinet drywall were damaged with the removal and installation . These areas should have been protected with tape or barriers before the work started.
2. The heater closet door was left with greese handprints inside an outside as was the door used to enter and exit the work area.
3. The new thermostat was not mounted  flush with the wall. The plastic molly dry wall inserts were sticking out about 1/8 inch and therefore the thermostat wall plate did not sit flush against the wall. I had to remove the thermostat to fill the old mounting holes and to paint the area because the new thermostat is smaller than the old thermostat. I had to replace the plastic molly inserts and reinstall the thermostat.
I did not catch thes issues until i got home at the end of the day. I was not at home for the whole installation process.
It is clear that these service representatives are well trained and capable technically but I expected a higher level of overall attention to detail. That level of attention is most likely not taught in the training they receive and in my opinion has to be part of the basic makeup of the individual, part of his personal performance DNA if you will.
Overall I was comfortable with the work done and would have Service Champions back in my house. I am a gold member, SC does the yearly system inspections and services my HVAC units. < Review>
I have a Trane XE70 gas furnance and it hasn't been working properly. I called Service Champions due to their history in the area and an add in the mail to come out, complete a tune up, and diagnose the problem. This was back in 2010 and the technician did the "tune up" and stated I needed a new furnance that would run me around $15k. He stated however if I just mess with a couple of wires the heater would ignite. I didn't bother doing anything with it since I was able to pull on some wires (recommended by a Service Champion employee which is a liability in itself) however this latest season has been pretty cold and pulling on the wires has not been working very well. I did 10-15 minutes research online and discovered I just need to replace the gas valve part #VAL09377 as per a diagnosis from a Trane technician who knew of this common problem with this model furnance. I called Service Champions and advised of the last visit in 2010 that was very unhelpful and seemed as prior reviews a scam and was blown off told that it was back in 2010 and they are under different management (same company). I was told they would take a whole $30 off of another visit (I live 2 miles away from their store) and it would only cost $40 to come back out. I told them I might call them back. I am in the customer service industry and this is by far not the way to take care of a situation like this. When a customer calls again even after feeling taken advantage of, try to give you another chance for a sale, and they express a concern why would you not try to make it right or direct the customer's concern to someone that can? I would not recommend this company to ANYONE. Do your own research online to diagnose the problem and then call around for an estimate for the labor only. Buy the part yourself.</Review>
